  "chapter": {
    "number": 51,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judgment on Babylon"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Behold, I will stir up against Babylon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and against the people of Leb-kamai",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3015
          },
          {
            "text": "the spirit of a destroyer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will send strangers to Babylon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to winnow her and empty her land;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for they will come against her from every side",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in her day of disaster.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not let the archer bend his bow",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or put on his armor.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not spare her young men;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "devote all her army to destruction!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3016
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And they will fall slain in the land of the Chaldeans,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3017
          },
          {
            "text": "and pierced through in her streets.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For Israel and Judah have not been abandoned",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "by their God, the LORD of Hosts,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "though their land is full of guilt",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "before the Holy One of Israel.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Flee from Babylon! Escape with your lives!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not be destroyed in her punishment.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For this is the time of the LORD’s vengeance;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will pay her what she deserves.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Babylon was a gold cup in the hand of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "making the whole earth drunk.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The nations drank her wine;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "therefore the nations have gone mad.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Suddenly Babylon has fallen and been shattered.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Wail for her; get her balm for her pain;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "perhaps she can be healed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“We tried to heal Babylon,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but she could not be healed.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Abandon her!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Let each of us go to his own land,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for her judgment extends to the sky",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and reaches to the clouds.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“The LORD has brought forth our vindication;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "come, let us tell in Zion",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "what the LORD our God has accomplished.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sharpen the arrows!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Fill the quivers!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3018
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD has aroused the spirit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of the kings of the Medes,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because His plan is aimed at Babylon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to destroy her,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for it is the vengeance of the LORD—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "vengeance for His temple.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Raise a banner against the walls of Babylon;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "post the guard;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "station the watchmen;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "prepare the ambush.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the LORD has both devised and accomplished",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "what He spoke against the people of Babylon.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You who dwell by many waters,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rich in treasures,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "your end has come;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the thread of your life is cut.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "The LORD of Hosts has sworn by Himself:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Surely I will fill you up with men as with locusts,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will shout in triumph over you.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Praise to the God of Jacob"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD made the earth by His power;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He established the world by His wisdom",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and stretched out the heavens by His understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When He thunders,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the waters in the heavens roar;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He causes the clouds to rise",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the ends of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He generates the lightning with the rain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and brings forth the wind from His storehouses.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Every man is senseless and devoid of knowledge;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "every goldsmith is put to shame by his idols.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For his molten images are a fraud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there is no breath in them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are worthless, a work to be mocked.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "In the time of their punishment they will perish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Portion of Jacob is not like these,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for He is the Maker of all things,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and of the tribe of His inheritance—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD of Hosts is His name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Babylon’s Punishment"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“You are My war club,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My weapon for battle.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "With you I shatter nations;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with you I bring kingdoms to ruin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "With you I shatter the horse and rider;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with you I shatter the chariot and driver.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "With you I shatter man and woman;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with you I shatter the old man and the youth;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with you I shatter the young man and the maiden.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "With you I shatter the shepherd and his flock;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with you I shatter the farmer and his oxen;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with you I shatter the governors and officials.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Before your very eyes I will repay",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Babylon and all the dwellers of Chaldea",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3019
          },
          {
            "text": "for all the evil they have done in Zion,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Behold, I am against you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O destroying mountain,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you who devastate the whole earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will stretch out My hand against you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will roll you over the cliffs",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and turn you into a charred mountain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No one shall retrieve from you a cornerstone",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or a foundation stone,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because you will become desolate forever,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Raise a banner in the land!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Blow the ram’s horn among the nations!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Prepare the nations against her.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Summon the kingdoms against her—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Ararat, Minni, and Ashkenaz.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Appoint a captain against her;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "bring up horses like swarming locusts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the nations for battle against her—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the kings of the Medes,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their governors and all their officials,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all the lands they rule.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The earth quakes and writhes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because the LORD’s intentions against Babylon stand:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to make the land of Babylon a desolation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "without inhabitant.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The warriors of Babylon have stopped fighting;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they sit in their strongholds.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their strength is exhausted;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have become like women.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Babylon’s homes have been set ablaze,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the bars of her gates are broken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "One courier races to meet another,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and messenger follows messenger,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to announce to the king of Babylon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that his city has been captured from end to end.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The fords have been seized,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the marshes set on fire,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the soldiers are terrified.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the LORD of Hosts, the God of Israel, says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“The Daughter of Babylon is like a threshing floor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "at the time it is trampled.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In just a little while",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her harvest time will come.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has devoured me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he has crushed me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has set me aside like an empty vessel;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he has swallowed me like a monster;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he filled his belly with my delicacies",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and vomited me out.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3020
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 35,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May the violence done to me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to my flesh",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "be upon Babylon,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says the dweller of Zion.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“May my blood be on the dwellers of Chaldea,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 36,
        "content": [
          "Therefore this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Behold, I will plead your case",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and take vengeance on your behalf;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will dry up her sea",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and make her springs run dry.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 37,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Babylon will become a heap of rubble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a haunt for jackals,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3021
          },
          {
            "text": "an object of horror and scorn,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "without inhabitant.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 38,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will roar together like young lions;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will growl like lion cubs.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 39,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "While they are flushed with heat,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will serve them a feast,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will make them drunk",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that they may revel;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "then they will fall asleep forever and never wake up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 40,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will bring them down like lambs to the slaughter,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like rams with male goats.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 41,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How Sheshach",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3022
          },
          {
            "text": "has been captured!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "The praise of all the earth has been seized.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "What a horror Babylon has become",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "among the nations!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 42,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The sea has come up over Babylon;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "she is covered in turbulent waves.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 43,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Her cities have become a desolation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a dry and arid land,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
